oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Chapman and Company store
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Exterior of Chapman and Company store in Pisgah, Tennessee. There is a group of males, approximately aged 3-45, on the porch of the store with two children pulling a horse and wagon in front of the store. There is a man in the street holding a foal with another horse and wagon in the background. One of the men is identified as Henry Randolph.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Stores & shops; Carts & wagons; Horses; Dry goods stores ; Signs (Notices)
